    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For `blue` to be applied to all indices, it needs to be at the top level. Only child indices receive the refinements, not scoped indices. This is therefore by design.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nsearch.addWidgets([\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: '#color-list',\r\n    attribute: 'color',\r\n  }),\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.index({ indexName: 'products' }).addWidgets([\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n      container: '#hits-products',\r\n      templates: {\r\n        item: `\r\n        <div>\r\n          <div class=\"hit-name\">\r\n            {{#helpers.highlight}}{ \"attribute\": \"name\" }{{/helpers.highlight}} // {{color}}\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      `,\r\n      },\r\n    }),\r\n  ]),\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.index({ indexName: 'banners' }).addWidgets([\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n      container: '#hits-banners',\r\n      templates: {\r\n        item: `\r\n        <div>\r\n          <div class=\"hit-name\">\r\n            {{#helpers.highlight}}{ \"attribute\": \"name\" }{{/helpers.highlight}} // {{color}}\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      `,\r\n      },\r\n    }),\r\n  ]),\r\n]);\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2019-11-28T15:22:29Z",
